db_browser(25.10)                                            db_browser(25.10)

Name
       db_browser - Launches the database browser (DB Browser)

Syntax
       db_browser

       [-help]

       <obj_list> | head | top | selected

       Launches  the database browser (DB Browser). The DB browser returns in-
       formation about one of the following:

              * Specified object list

              * Root of the database

              * Top cell of the design

              * Selected object

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each db_browser parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man db_browser

       <obj_list>  | head | top | selected
              Specifies the objects whose attributes need to be  displayed  in
              the browser:

              * obj_list: Displays attributes of the list of specified objects
                in  the browser. Use the Show next object in list and the Show
                last object in list buttons in the browser to traverse through
                the list.

              * head: Displays technology information about the  root  of  the
                database in the browser.

              * top:  Displays attributes of the top cell of the design in the
                browser

              * selected: Displays attributes of the objects you have selected
                in the main window. Use the Show next object in list button in
                the DB Browser to move to the next object in the sequence.

Examples
              * The following command launches the DB Browser and returns  at-
                tributes of the top cell of the design.

                db_browser top

Related Information
              * Edit Menu chapter in the Innovus Menu Reference

                * DB Browser

